 "_notes": [
  "MACRO-BLOCKED CHUNKS (do NOT force these defect counts down with the local patch loop — they need the macro connectivity/bridge pass, CRITICAL_PATH.md Steps 4-5): The whole NW 'Goblin Wilds' north of the Willow river is a large region stranded from spawn (audit_world warns ~7642-tile pocket near 72,106). Because of it: c0,r1 has dead_pocket (67,105) size 424 — reachable across a single river channel at (58,124)→(58,125), so ONE authored footbridge/ford reclaims all 424 tiles; and sealed_room (80,129) sits INSIDE the stranded region, so punching a door won't un-seal it until the region connects. The treeline slivers at x70-74 / x78-79 y135-199 are a dense 2-3-deep wall on the river's west bank; their sealed trees only un-seal by punching multiple gaps, low value until the bridge lands. RECOMMEND: the macro pass decides where the Wilds bridge goes (a ford near x58,y124 is the natural spot), then the local loop mops up the slivers. Until then leave c0,r1 as-is."
 ],
